sql:
SELECT p.id, p.name, p.popularity
FROM participants p
LEFT JOIN performance_score ps ON p.id = ps.participant_id
GROUP BY p.id, p.name, p.popularity
ORDER BY COUNT(ps.songs_id) DESC;
question: What are the ids, names and popularity of the participants, order by the number of songs they perform?

sql:
SELECT p.id, p.name, p.popularity, COUNT(ps.songs_id) AS song_count
FROM participants p
LEFT JOIN performance_score ps ON p.id = ps.participant_id
GROUP BY p.id, p.name, p.popularity
ORDER BY song_count DESC;

sql:
SELECT p.id, p.name, p.popularity, COUNT(ps.songs_id) AS songs_performed
FROM participants p
